page_title: "Set up Advanced Network Observability for Azure Kubernetes Service (AKS) - Azure managed Prometheus and Grafana"
page_description: Get started with Advanced Network Observability for your AKS cluster using Azure managed Prometheus and Grafana.
chunk_content:
Create a resource group

A resource group is a logical container into which Azure resources are deployed and managed. Create a resource group using the `az group create` command.

```azurecli-interactive
# Set environment variables for the resource group name and location. Make sure to replace the placeholders with your own values.
export RESOURCE_GROUP="<resource-group-name>"
export LOCATION="<azure-region>"

# Create a resource group
az group create --name $RESOURCE_GROUP --location $LOCATION
```
